  "chapter": {
    "number": 35,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Glory of Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wilderness and the land will be glad;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the desert will rejoice and blossom like a rose.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It will bloom profusely",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and rejoice with joy and singing.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The glory of Lebanon will be given to it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the splendor of Carmel and Sharon.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will see the glory of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the splendor of our God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Strengthen the limp hands",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and steady the feeble knees!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2628
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Say to those with anxious hearts:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Be strong, do not fear!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Behold, your God will come with vengeance.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "With divine retribution He will come to save you.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the eyes of the blind will be opened",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the ears of the deaf unstopped.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the lame will leap like a deer",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the mute tongue will shout for joy.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For waters will gush forth in the wilderness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and streams in the desert.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The parched ground will become a pool,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the thirsty land springs of water.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "In the haunt where jackals",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2629
          },
          {
            "text": "once lay,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there will be grass and reeds and papyrus.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And there will be a highway",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "called the Way of Holiness.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The unclean will not travel it—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "only those who walk in the Way—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and fools will not stray onto it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No lion will be there,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and no vicious beast will go up on it.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Such will not be found there,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the redeemed will walk upon it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So the redeemed of the LORD will return",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and enter Zion with singing,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "crowned with everlasting joy.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Gladness and joy will overtake them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sorrow and sighing will flee.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
